@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@clerkToken = PASTE_YOUR_CLERK_JWT_HERE
@projectId = PASTE_PROJECT_ID_HERE

### Health Check (v1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health

### Test — No Token (should 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me

### Test — Bad Token (should 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me
Authorization: Bearer this.is.not.valid

### Get Current User (Me)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}

### Update Profile
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bio": "Full-stack developer building cool things",
  "location": "Mumbai, India",
  "website": "https://example.com",
  "isPublic": true
}

### List Projects
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}

### Create Project
# Use the returned "id" in the @projectId variable above
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "DevTrack V2",
  "description": "Engineering growth OS",
  "deadline": "2026-08-01T00:00:00Z"
}

### Create Task
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Build GitHub sync pipeline",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "dueDate": "2026-06-15T00:00:00Z"
}

### Archive Project (Soft Delete)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/archive
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}

### List Repositories
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/github/repositories
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}

### Get Sync Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/github/status
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}

### Get Current Streak
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/streak
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}

### Get Analytics Summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}

### Get Language Breakdown
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/languages
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}

### Create Learning Log
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/learning
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "topic": "NestJS EventEmitter2",
  "notes": "Learned how to use wildcard events for domain-driven design",
  "source": "https://docs.nestjs.com/techniques/events",
  "tags": ["nestjs", "backend", "events"],
  "duration": 90
}

### List Learning Logs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/learning
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}

### AI Complete (Growth Insight)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{clerkToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "I have made 42 commits in the last 7 days, mostly in TypeScript. Give me one specific, actionable growth insight in 3 sentences.",
  "maxTokens": 256
}
